def_cn: (美国、澳大利亚等国议会的)参议院
def_en: The Senate is the smaller and more important of the two parts of the parliament in some countries, for example the United States and Australia.  →see usage note at:government

def_cn: （某些大学的）大学理事会，大学评议会
def_en: Senate or the Senate is the governing council at some universities.
